  "description": [
    "4 hams _ s _ with his whip The Budl of yesterday gives another version of the story which issaid to rest 5 on good authority and to be more correct than the one we published ifso we can only say that we agree with our opponent in the opinion that the Magistrate did no more than his duty RA in imposing the fine It appears extraordinary es however that a gentleman in the civil service of the Company should set an example of such treatment of the natives when it is the duty of all in that service more particularly to inculcate both by example and precept a conduct the very a reverse towards our timid native subjects and j to demonstrate to them on all occasions that their its rights ar\u00e9 asmuch respected as those of any other class of subjects 4 As for the exactions of the Chowkeydars it has been our lot to give publicity to many facts in illustration of it but we never could learn that any investigation was the result We have strong reason to believe that the most shameful extortion is practised by these myrmidons of the 4 police upon the poor"
